@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

                            @{u}Introduction@{uu}

YAM's MIME support is not especially strong and can only by default
do one preset command per attachment. With the use of its extensive
ARexx interface however it can become a lot more powerful and this
is an attempt at showing such strength.

The idea itself emerged from having been fed up with first having to
save the attachment - in this case an archived file - to then open a
CLI window and extract it. It had to be ways that it could be made
easier not to mention quicker. It was.

A few hours work and MIMEhandler was born. But it was very basic and
lacked one important feature; easy configuration. So back to the
drawing table and an additional day's worth of work and MIMEhandlerII
was born. Now with an easy and powerful configuration.
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"

                            @{u}Features@{uu}

A look at what features this script currently inhibits:

 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} Handles multipart attachments
 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} Extensive @{"configuration" link "Configuration"}
 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} All commands one would expect (perhaps) such as:
   View, Extract, Save and Delete individual attachments
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"

                            @{u}Requirements@{uu}

Required software are these:

 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} YAM (@{"http://www.yam.ch/" system "run openurl TOFRONT LAUNCH URL http://www.yam.ch/"})
   (Preferably 2.0Preview7 or later for that is the one the author has
    tested this script with.)
 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} RexxReqTools (@{"aminet:util/rexx/RexxReqTools.lha" system "run openurl TOFRONT LAUNCH URL http://ftp.uni-paderborn.de/aminet/dirs/util/rexx/RexxReqTools.lha"})
   (For file requestors when saving/extracting.)
 @{fg shine}o@{fg text} Any file handler for the MIME types you wish to use you can find.

@{i}The above links uses the excellent program OpenURL by Troels Walsted Hansen
<troels@stud.cs.uit.no> available in aminet:util/misc/OpenURL.lha @{ui}
@endnode

